        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 4:16PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Brookneal, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail and wind gusts up to 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Loose items may be knocked over by wind gusts.

Locations impacted include...
Brookneal...
Charlotte Court House...
Phenix...
Red House...
Nathalie...
Cody...
and Cullen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
